    public boolean validate(){   //The function declaration for validation. It should ideally involve hashing & comparing passwords stored in database against inputted one (because we don’t have a real DB here).  The return type of this method will be 'boolean' to indicate whether the credential is valid or not
        /* This part may contain your logic based on requirement */    //The code should ideally involve hashing & comparing passwords stored in database against inputted one (because we don’t have a real DB here). The return type of this method will be 'boolean' to indicate whether the credential is valid or not
        /* This part may contain your logic based on requirement */    //To prevent SQL Injection attacks, you should never store passwords in plain text. Use hash algorithms such as SHA-256 and compare hashes (for instance). For XSS protection use escaping functions like HTML escape/encode etc
        return false;   /* default value which may be replaced by your logic */ //Should ideally involve comparing inputted username & password with the one stored in database against some sort of hash or salt. If they match, then validate() should now just say 'return true' and else it would mean that credential is not valid so return false
    }//End Of Main Function Declaration for Validation 
